76561198260705384,Recommended,271970,22903933,"Posted: 10 May, 2016",all,GethN7,"This is a great game, and as someone who who works a lot with RPG Maker VX Ace, I'm amazed how good it is.The plot is cliche and won;t win awards, it's the bog standard RPG cliche of toppling some random dark lord, but that aside, this game is very aware of it's cliches and mocks the crap out of them.Of course, it's kinda meta, but even that isn't all. This game has the unique twist you are Level 1 and cannot gain levels at all, meaning you have to farm stat boosters and rely on allies (if you are into waifus, which all your allies are, you will have fun getting them all, like a non pornographic Pokemon meets harem anime, though it's a bit ecchi though, be warned if that turns you off)The gameplay is mix of Diablo style dungeon crawling (with maps that are semi-random like the bonus dungeons in Final Fantasy 1 & 2 Dawn of Souls and classic front view RPG turn based combat, though with the twist all you allies are very specialized and you must pick and choose wisely.However, you must try to keep all your summoned waifus leveled and well equipped, as the game includes a sim element where you ""level up"" a village, and as you do, the village get attacked from time to time, with the waifu force as the defenders, so can't just bench and ignore part of your harem force either.It's very forgiving for the most part, so a noob need not fear jumping in, it's pretty self explanatory on the game mechanics and while it's a pain to keep your main character from dying early on, the game includes tons of ways to make him not suck so much, not to mention is kinda encourages you to have the waifus do most of the work anyway.Overall, it won't win awards for originality, but it's VERY fun in a Diablo style way, and as a big Diablo II fan, this game is like that, just more colorful, slightly easier, and with a lot of waifus as support."
